Your _add_ method, or more correctly, _addNode_ method, is not doing anything to the instance.

It is effectively assigning the parameter _head_ to, the _next_ value of parameter, _node_.

```java
void addNode(Node node, Node head) {
    node.next = head;
}
```

The _push_ method is correct, it will stack the object before the instance&#39;s _head_ node.


You can remove the the _addNode_ method, and for the _add_ method, it only requires 1 parameter.

You&#39;ll want to locate the last node in the structure, and then append the parameter to it.

```java
void add(Node node) {
    Node lastNode = this.head;
    while (lastNode.next != null) lastNode = lastNode.next;
    lastNode.next = node;
}
```

